results.name: Kyrie 7 GS 'Chinese New Year'
results.story: The Nike Kyrie 7 GS ‘Chinese New Year’ delivers a celebratory colorway of Kyrie Irving’s seventh signature shoe made for big kids. In a nod to the lunar holiday, the sneaker’s heel overlay is accented with a red Chinese knot, superimposed with an embroidered gold Swoosh. A larger knotted gold Swoosh adorns the lateral side of the upper, built with pink and blue mesh. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a Phylon midsole, its sidewalls wrapped up by a data-inspired rubber outsole.

results.name: Wmns NikeCourt Air Max Volley 'White Purple Gradient'
Zoom Freak 2 'Play for the Future'
results.story: The Nike Zoom Freak 2 'Play for the Future' draws inspiration from Nike Basketball’s commitment to uplifting a new generation of stars — a vision shared by Giannis Antetokounmpo, who used to split one pair of basketball between himself and his brothers. The low-top makes use of a sapphire textile upper, accented with neon green detailing and mounted atop a midsole that combines soft foam with Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot. A molded TPU piece on the lateral sidewall is designed to contain Giannis’ signature Euro step move.

results.name: LeBron 18 EP 'Play For The Future'
results.story: The Nike LeBron 18 EP ‘Play for the Future’ clads the hoops shoe in breezy sky blue tones, a nod to the clean, unpolluted air required by current and future generations of athletes. An integrated lacing system secures the KnitPosite 2.0 upper, equipped with a stretchy collar and molded TPU heel counter. The cushioning system combines a Cushlon midsole with a full-length Zoom Air unit, the back of which is housed within a visible Max Air unit in the heel. This EP version is exclusive to Asia and features an extra-durable rubber outsole made for play on outdoor courts.

results.name: Kyrie 7 GS 'Play for the Future'
results.story: Constructed for big kids, the Nike Kyrie 7 ‘Play for the Future’ takes inspiration from Kyrie Irving’s commitment to a sustainable lifestyle, including his vegan diet. In addition to a plant-based color scheme, the heel overlay is embroidered with a sprouted KI logo. Laces are looped into molded forefoot fins for a lockdown fit, while the midsole packs soft foam in the forefoot for plush cushioning and firmer foam in the heel for improved stability. A bright turquoise outsole wraps up the sidewalls for maximum grip.

results.name: Cosmic Unity EP 'Amalgam'
results.story: The Nike Cosmic Unity EP ‘Amalgam’ highlights a vibrant palette on a performance hoops shoe built with sustainability in mind. Made with 25% recycled content by weight, the low-top features a durable textile knit upper in a bright Sapphire hue. The padded collar and perforated tongue are rendered in Glacier Blue, while webbing straps are rendered in eye-catching Atomic Orange. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a partially recycled Air Zoom Strobel. This EP version is available exclusively in Asia and features an extra-durable herringbone outsole made for outdoor use.

results.name: Kyrie 7 'Play for the Future'
results.story: Inspired by Kyrie Irving’s vegan lifestyle, the Nike Kyrie 7 ‘Play for the Future’ features plant-inspired graphics throughout the orange mesh upper, as well as a ‘sprouted’ KI logo embroidered on the heel overlay. In terms of performance, the midsole houses a large forefoot Zoom Air unit for responsive cushioning in all directions. A turquoise finish is applied to the rubber outsole, which wraps up the sidewalls for added traction during quick movements on the hardwood.

results.name: PG 5 EP 'Play for the Future'
results.story: Inspired by the planet’s most critical natural resource, the Nike PG 5 EP ‘Play for the Future’ outfits Paul George’s signature shoe with a textile upper covered in watery green hues and a subtle ripple graphic on the quarter panel. The low-top is equipped with a padded collar and multicolor laces that feed into midfoot bands, providing an increasingly locked-in fit as the laces are tightened. Responsive cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length Nike Air Dot Weld Strobel that’s stitched directly to the upper. This EP version features an extra-durable rubber outsole made for outdoor play.

results.name: Zoom Freak 2 EP 'Play for the Future'
Nike Cosmic Unity Amalgam
results.story: The Nike Cosmic Unity ‘Amalgam’ highlights a vibrant palette on a performance hoops shoe released under the brand’s environmentally-minded Move to Zero initiative. The sneaker features 25% recycled content by weight, a figure achieved in part by using a royal blue textile upper made with recycled cable yarn. The mint green speckled midsole is constructed from proprietary foams and roughly 10% Nike Grind, while the full-length Zoom Air Strobel utilizes recycled TPU. Even the laces, sockliner, and marble Swoosh incorporate recycled materials.

results.name: Mercurial Dream Speed Superfly 8 Elite FG 'Bright Mango'
PG 5 'Play for the Future'
results.story: In recognition of the importance of clean water, the Nike PG 5 ‘Play for the Future’ dresses Paul George’s signature shoe with a textile upper finished in aqueous green hues. A subtle ripple-like graphic on the quarter amplifies the water-conservation theme. The sneaker’s performance benefits include a full-length Nike Air Dot Weld Strobel and an integrated lacing system for midfoot lockdown. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a multi-directional tread for stop-and-go traction on the hardwood.

results.name: LeBron 8 TD 'Graffiti'
results.story: The Nike LeBron 8 TD ‘Graffiti’ delivers a scaled-down version of a PE model that LeBron James debuted in an exhibition game during the 2011 NBA lockout. Inspired by an ultra-limited LeBron 4 colorway from 2006, the textile upper is secured with a midfoot strap and covered in a graffiti-print textile upper. The black and white design is offset by contrasting Sport Red hits on the collar lining, signature Swoosh and Flywire cables. A soft foam midsole is reinforced by a grippy red rubber outsole.

results.name: Force Zoom Trout 7 TF 'Game Royal'
results.story: The Nike Force Zoom Trout 7 TF ‘Game Royal’ delivers a team-oriented two-tone colorway of Mike Trout’s signature training shoe. An integrated lacing system secures a blue mesh upper, accented with a white Swoosh and reinforced with translucent TPU cages at the heel and midfoot. Both extend to the foam midsole, fitted with a dual-chambered Zoom Air unit in the heel. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features an aggressive tread designed for pre-game surfaces.

results.name: Force Zoom Trout 7 Pro Mid 'White Metallic Silver'
results.story: Designed to contain the speed and power of MLB slugger Mike Trout, the Nike Force Zoom Trout 7 Pro Mid ‘White Metallic Silver’ treats the performance baseball cleat to a pristine color palette. A Ghost Lace system combines with a midfoot strap to secure the white mesh upper, reinforced with a durable synthetic skin and a translucent TPU heel cage. The midsole packs visible Zoom Air pods in the forefoot and heel, the latter featuring a springy inner chamber housed within a larger chamber for impact protection. A tuned underfoot plate features metal studs that dig into grass or turf.

results.name: Blazer Low '77 PS 'White Midnight Navy'
results.story: Crafted for little kids, the Nike Blazer Low ‘77 PS ‘White Midnight Navy’ steps out in an elemental two-tone colorway. The white leather upper is reinforced with tonal suede overlays and secured with traditional laces and an added hook-and-loop strap that wraps over the midfoot. Contrasting navy hits land on the sneaker’s branding elements, including the signature retro Swoosh and a Nike wordmark on the heel tab. Underfoot, a herringbone gum rubber outsole provides grippy traction.

results.name: Nike Dunk High PRM Dark Russet
results.story: The Nike Dunk High Premium ‘Dark Curry’ showcases warm, autumnal tones on a sneaker that began as a performance hoops shoe in 1985 and re-emerged decades later as a streetwear staple. The high-top features a Velvet Brown suede upper with a burnt orange Swoosh and shaggy suede overlays in Dark Russet. The sneaker is mounted on a durable rubber cupsole, undergirded by a traction pattern made for pivoting on the hardwood.

results.name: Nike Air Force 1 Low Craft Galactic Jade
results.story: The Nike Air Force 1 ’07 Craft ‘Galactic Jade’ treats the classic silhouette to a simple two-tone color scheme with subtly refreshed branding elements. A dark green finish is applied to the tumbled leather upper, contrasted by navy suede accents on the Swoosh and heel tab. The latter is left deliberately blank, while AF1 branding is transposed to a smaller attached flap. An updated Air Force 1 logo adorns the woven tongue tag and sockliner. The sneaker rests on an off-white rubber cupsole with encapsulated Nike Air cushioning.

results.name: Force Zoom Trout 7 TF 'University Red'
results.story: The Nike Force Zoom Trout 7 TF ‘University Red’ delivers a simple two-tone colorway of Mike Trout’s signature training shoe. Crimson knit textile is utilized on the upper, secured with an integrated lacing system and fortified with a translucent TPU cage around the midfoot and heel. The latter extends to a dual-chambered Zoom Air unit that provides both impact protection and springy cushioning. Underfoot, a decoupled rubber outsole provides flexible traction on pre-game surfaces.

results.name: Force Zoom Trout 7 Pro Mid 'University Red'
Nike Dunk Low SP City Market
results.story: The Nike Dunk Low ‘City Market’ pays tribute to temporary street markets and the industrial packaging used to ship their various wares, including rice and coffee bags that are typically upcycled for miscellaneous use. Those burlap vessels are recreated on some of the mismatched textile panels that make up the composition of the upper, while colorful graphics give the nod to Blue Ribbon Sports, Nike’s precursor brand. A nutrition label-like tag adorns the tongue, which is equipped with a zippered compartment inspired by reusable grocery totes. Additional details include a transparent Swoosh and a graphic on the left sockliner that states ‘Thank you for caring!’

results.name: Nike SB Dunk Low Supreme Stars Black (2021)
results.story: The Supreme x Nike Dunk Low OG SB QS ‘Black’ represents an homage to the partner brands’ Dunk High release from 2003. The low-top brings back virtually every key feature of the older shoe, including a white leather base, printed gold stars and contrast-colored overlays in croc-embossed leather. Gold Nike hits at the heel tab and woven tongue tag are matched by a gilded Supreme lace jewel. Inside the shoe, Supreme and Nike SB branding decorates the custom sockliner, finished in a bold red hue and fitted with a Zoom Air unit for lightweight cushioning.

results.name: Nike SB Dunk Low Supreme Stars Mean Green (2021)
results.story: The Supreme x Nike Dunk Low OG SB QS ‘Mean Green’ represents one of four colorways to release as the spiritual sequel to the partner brands’ 2003 Dunk High collaboration. Like the original, this pair features a white leather base with printed gold stars and croc-embossed leather overlays, rendered here in a vibrant green hue. A molded Supreme lace jewel in metallic gold is matched by Nike logo hits at the heel tab and woven tongue tag. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a Zoom Air unit in the custom sockliner, featuring a crimson surface marked with dual Supreme and Nike SB branding.

results.name: Nike SB Dunk Low Supreme Stars Barkroot Brown (2021)
results.story: The Supreme x Nike Dunk Low OG SB QS ‘Barkroot Brown’ features a familiar design inspired by the brands’ Dunk High collaboration from 2003, released during the height of the Silver Box era. Like the original, the shoe features a white leather upper, printed gold stars, stuffed textile tongue, flat black laces, a gold Supreme lace jewel, and croc-embossed leather overlays, finished here in a rich brown hue. Inside the shoe, dual Supreme and Nike SB branding decorates the red sockliner, featuring a Zoom Air unit in the heel for responsive cushioning.

results.name: Nike SB Dunk Low Supreme Stars Hyper Royal (2021)
results.story: The Supreme x Nike Dunk Low OG SB QS ‘Hyper Royal’ takes direct inspiration from the New York skate brand’s Dunk High collaboration from 2003. Like the high-top, this pair features a white leather base with metallic gold stars on the quarter panels and croc-embossed leather overlays in a contrasting hue. A standard Nike wordmark is embroidered in gold lettering on the heel tab, matching the woven tag atop the stuffed textile tongue. A gold Supreme dubrae shines at the bottom of the lace bed. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a Zoom Air-infused sockliner, its crimson surface embellished with dual Supreme and Nike SB branding.

results.name: Phantom GT Pro FG 'Black Cyber'
results.story: A performance soccer cleat made for short-grass fields, the Nike Phantom GT Pro FG ‘Black Cyber’ makes use of a pliant Flyknit upper that wraps the foot in a snug, sock-like fit. Off-center lacing creates a cleaner strike zone, while the coated surface features a slightly raised texture for improved control when passing, dribbling and shooting. Underfoot, the outsole plate features a mix of conical and chevron-shaped studs for superior grip.

PG 5 'White Black'
results.story: The Nike PG 5 ‘White Black’ updates Paul George’s fifth signature shoe with an essential two-tone palette that accentuates the clean lines of the minimalist low-top. Breathable white textile is utilized on the upper, secured with an integrated lacing system for a locked-in fit. The sneaker’s cushioning technology is carried over from the PG 4, featuring a full-length Nike Air Dot Weld Strobel stitched directly to the upper. Underfoot, the rubber outsole uses a multidirectional tread for grippy stop-and-go traction.

Waffle Trainer 2 SP 'Starfish'
results.story: The Nike Waffle Trainer 2 SP ‘Starfish’ brings back the 1977 running shoe in a simple two-tone color scheme and a contemporary build. A vibrant orange hue is executed on the nylon and suede upper, equipped with an exposed foam tongue and accented with a contrasting black Swoosh. A memory foam sockliner works in tandem with a dual-density foam midsole to deliver soft cushioning and a smooth ride. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features the iconic waffle tread that gives the shoe its name.

Nike Blazer Mid READYMADE Black
results.story: Designed in partnership with Yuta Hosokawa’s menswear brand, the READYMADE x Nike Blazer Mid ‘Black Camo’ reinvents the retro hoops shoe as a DIY assemblage of leftover pieces. Multiple laces secure an upper built with camo-like textile, overlaid with unfinished quarter panels and a distorted orange Swoosh that wraps around the READYMADE branded heel. Exposed foam on the tongue and collar adds to the sneaker’s deconstructed look. A bumpy texture distinguishes the rubber midsole, which gives way a herringbone traction outsole made with recycled Nike Grind material.

results.name: Air Max 90 Leather PS 'Black Sunset Pulse'
results.story: Crafted for little kids, the Nike Air Max 90 Leather PS ‘Black Sunset Pulse’ updates the vintage silhouette with a black leather upper, accented with a metallic silver Swoosh and TPU detailing in sapphire and hot pink. The sneaker rides on a plush foam midsole with a visible Max Air unit in the heel. Underfoot, the rubber outsole is equipped with a classic waffle tread and a series of deep flex grooves, good for superior traction and a smooth, comfortable ride.

results.name: Wmns React Escape Run 'Vast Grey Pink Glaze'
results.story: Built on a last developed specifically for the female foot, the Nike women’s React Escape Run ‘Vast Grey Pink Glaze’ pairs pastel accents with an otherwise neutral color scheme. A subtle grey finish floods the minimalist mesh upper, featuring semi-translucent midfoot paneling and a wider collar that accommodates the forward placement of the female ankle. Plush cushioning is provided by a stacked Nike React midsole, bolstered underfoot by a grippy gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Wmns Metcon 6 'Football Grey Arctic Punch'
results.story: The Nike women’s Metcon 6 ‘Football Grey Arctic Punch’ uses a delicate pink hue as a display of fortitude. The pastel finish is applied to the training shoe’s rubber outsole, featuring a wide, stable platform and extended coverage that wraps up the sneaker’s sidewalls, a signature attribute of the Metcon line. The upper is built with a lightweight mesh forefoot, reinforced with a durable screen print and offering 18% more breathability than the Metcon 5.

results.name: Tiempo Legend 8 Club MG GS 'Platinum Tint Rage Green'
results.story: The Nike Tiempo Legend 8 Club MG GS ‘Platinum Tint Rage Green’ delivers a simplistic two-tone colorway of a grade-school soccer cleat made for short-grass and artificial surfaces. The streamlined upper combines coated textile with durable synthetic leather, featuring a diamond texture that yields enhanced control for precise shooting, passing and dribbling. Underfoot, a series of green-tipped studs provide optimal stop-and-go traction.

results.name: Air Structure GS 'Black Smoke Grey'
results.story: The Nike Air Structure GS ‘Black Smoke Grey’ brings back the early ‘90s running shoe in a neutral colorway made for big kids. Breathable black mesh is utilized on the upper, reinforced with angular overlays in black nubuck and grey synthetic leather. A white leather Swoosh is matched by molded eyelets and Nike Air branding embroidered on the heel. The midsole is distinguished by an asymmetrical Max Air unit that’s configured differently on the sneaker’s medial and lateral side.

results.name: LeBron 8 PS 'Empire Jade'
results.story: Built for little kids, the Nike LeBron 8 PS ‘Empire Jade’ celebrates the 600th anniversary of Beijing’s Forbidden City, featuring an aged leather upper in a rich scarlet hue. Raw edges are stained yellow, matching LeBron James’ signature lion graphic embossed on the tongue. A contrasting black Swoosh is set farther back, so that its tapered tail extends to a pull tab affixed to the heel. Flywire-infused TPU panels provide lightweight support. The sneaker rides on a full-length Phylon midsole, coated in a pale green hue and reinforced by a matching glow-in-the-dark rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Max 95 Premium 'Crocodile Skin' By You
results.story: Available through the brand’s customization service, the Nike Air Max 95 Premium ‘Crocodile Skin’ By You dresses the sneaker’s layered side panels in croc-embossed leather, featuring an outer layer that eventually wears away to reveal an entirely different hue. The retro runner rides on a standard polyurethane midsole, fitted with visible Max Air units in the heel and forefoot, and reinforced by a waffled tread rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Max 95 By You
results.story: The Nike Air Max 95 By You is designed through the brand’s customization service and utilizes polished twill textile throughout the upper, accented with contrast Volt stitching that outlines the sneaker’s layered side panels. Rope laces are looped through webbing eyelets, partially concealed by a breathable mesh overlay. The retro silhouette rides on a lightweight polyurethane midsole, housing visible Max Air units in the heel and forefoot and supported by a waffle traction rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Structure GS 'Grey Fog Lapis'
results.story: The Nike Air Structure GS ‘Grey Fog Lapis’ celebrates the retro running shoe’s 30th anniversary with a simplistic color scheme made for big kids. The silhouette is heralded for its stable ride and distinctive lines, formed with black nubuck and grey leather overlays stitched atop a breathable white mesh base. Deep blue accents make their way to the sneaker’s molded eyelets, signature Swoosh and embroidered Nike Air branding on the heel. Performance benefits include a stabilizing heel counter and visible Max Air cushioning.

results.name: LeBron 8 TD 'Empire Jade'
results.story: The Nike LeBron 8 TD ‘Empire Jade’ delivers a scaled-down version of LeBron James’ eighth signature shoe, featuring a distinctive palette inspired by Beijing’s Forbidden City. A distressed finish is applied to the scarlet synthetic leather upper, secured with an adjustable midfoot strap for a custom fit. LeBron’s signature lion crest adorns the tongue, while a contrasting black Swoosh decorates the sneaker’s lateral side. Underfoot, a rubber outsole in Cucumber Calm provides grippy traction for little feet.

results.name: Phantom GT Club MG GS 'Photo Blue'
results.story: Built for big kids, the Nike Phantom GT Club MG GS ‘Photo Blue’ applies a vibrant finish to a soccer cleat made for both natural and synthetic surfaces. Off-center lacing on the synthetic leather upper yields a clean strike zone, while a grippy texture provides enhanced ball control when shooting, dribbling and passing. Underfoot, the multiground plate is equipped with neon green studs that provide grippy traction for quick acceleration and abrupt changes in movement.

results.name: Nike Blazer Mid READYMADE White
results.story: The READYMADE x Nike Blazer Mid ‘White Camo’ showcases a deconstructed build in keeping with the Japanese brand’s upcycled aesthetic. A half-stitched Swoosh, reconfigured with a pronounced curve and thinner shape, adorns an upper built with splotched foam and irregular side panels in a crisp white finish. More exposed foam tongue is utilized on the collar and tongue, the latter overlaid with three distinct sets of laces. The mid-top sits on a molded rubber midsole that gives way to a herringbone rubber outsole made in part with Nike Grind. READYMADE branding decorates the heel overlay and custom sockliner.

results.name: Tiempo Legend 8 Pro FG 'Black Siren Red Photo Blue'
results.story: A firm-ground performance soccer cleat, the Nike Tiempo Legend 8 Pro FG ‘Black Siren Red Photo Blue’ makes use of coated textile and premium calfskin leather on the upper. The latter material features seamless construction with a molded diamond texture for enhanced ball control. Soft microfiber lines the heel for non-slip comfort, while a molded sockliner provides lightweight cushioning. Underfoot, chevron and conical studs combine for multidirectional traction.

results.name: Nike Waffle One SE The Whitaker Group
Air Max 90 PS 'City Special - Chicago'
results.story: Dropping as part of the ‘City Special’ series, the Nike Air Max 90 PS ‘Chicago’ honors the City of Big Shoulders with a saturated colorway made for little kids. Varying crimson shades are executed on the layered upper, crafted from a blend of real and synthetic leather. ‘CHI’ is inscribed on the custom sockliner and a discreet woven tag affixed to the sneaker’s lateral side. The monochromatic palette extends to the polyurethane midsole, featuring visible Nike Air cushioning under the heel.

results.name: Air Max 97 'City Special - Los Angeles'
results.story: The Nike Air Max 97 ‘Los Angeles’ is drawn from the brand’s ‘City Special’ series, featuring multiple Air Max silhouettes draped in eye-catching monochromatic hues. This pair celebrates the City of Angels with a layered textile build in varying shades of orange, along with tonal synthetic overlays finished in a 3M reflective coating. Contrasting black hits land on the sneaker’s pull tabs and branding elements, which include a small woven ‘LA’ tag. Buoyant cushioning arrives via the AM97’s signature full-length Max Air unit.

results.name: Nike Air Max Up City Special NYC (W)
results.story: Releasing as part of the ‘City Special’ collection, the Nike women’s Air Max Up ‘NYC Lady Liberty’ honors the Big Apple with a bright green finish intended to evoke the Statue of Liberty’s oxidized copper exterior. Ripstop textile is utilized on the upper, featuring tonal no-sew overlays and partially concealed laces for a sleek aesthetic. ‘NYC’ is stamped on gold lace jewels and inscribed on a small woven tag on the lateral collar. The sneaker sits on a stacked foam midsole, enhanced with a large-volume Max Air unit housed within a TPU frame.

results.name: Blazer Low '77 Suede 'Midnight Navy'
results.story: The Nike Blazer Low ‘77 Suede ‘Midnight Navy’ features a simple two-tone color scheme in keeping with the shoe’s ‘70s hardwood roots. Navy suede construction on the upper is fortified with tonal overlays around the toe and forefoot. Contrasting white leather detailing appears on the retro Swoosh and Nike branded heel tab. A second Nike wordmark can be found on the woven tag stitched onto the exposed foam tongue, which combines with a low-cut collar for a comfortable fit.

results.name: Air Max 97 GS 'City Special - Los Angeles'
results.story: Developed for big kids, the Nike Air Max 97 GS ‘Los Angeles’ is one of several tonal Air Max styles that make up the brand’s ‘City Special’ collection. This LA-inspired colorway features an orange textile upper with a pair of wavy synthetic overlays in a reflective finish. The uniform color scheme is disrupted by contrasting black accents, including an embroidered mini-Swoosh on the quarter panel and webbing pull tabs at the tongue and heel. A small LA woven tag adorns the sneaker’s lateral side.

results.name: Wmns Free RN 5.0 By You
results.story: Designed via the brand’s customization platform, the Nike women’s Free RN 5.0 By You is built on a firm foam sole unit that uses deep cuts to deliver flexible cushioning and a natural stride. The seamless bootie-style upper is secured with off-center lacing for an optimal fit. No-sew overlays provide lightweight support and durability, while three foam pods are built into the interior heel that makes the back of the foot feel more comfortable and locked in.
